#subtitle: Building relations with the other political parties of Germany.

= Inter-Party Relationships

@interparty

The <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> cannot govern by itself yet, because we do not have an electoral majority. We can reach out and build additional connections with other parties, or perhaps we can stand alone.

- @nasrani: Work together with the <span style="color: #66B2FF;">Christian</span> and <span style="color: #660000;">Catholic </span>parties.
- @islam: The <span style="color: #000000;">Islamic</span> parties.
- @other: Strengthen our bonds with other smaller parties.
- @pki: Work towards repairing relationships with the <span style="color: #c00000;">Communist</span> Party.
- @pni_alone: The <span style="color: #990000;">PNI</span> can stand alone for now.
- @easy_discard

@pki
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; pki_relation += 5*(1 - dissent); sidik_strength += 3

The <span style="color: #c00000;">**Communists**</span> have always been our close ally, but we never get the chance to be in government together with them. However this may change.

@other
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; psi_relation += 5*(1 - dissent); pir_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

Though electorally small, allying the smaller parties like the <span style="color: #FF6666;">**PSI**</span> or the <span style="color: #FF9933;">**PIR**</span> can be crucial in forming cabinet coalitions.

@islam

- @masyumi_ties: Meet with their leadership to develop closer ties with the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span>.
- @sukiman_connections: Soekiman, the head of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> legislative branch, is more in line with our current leadership. Perhaps we can establish connections with him?
- @natsir_connections: Natsir, the head of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> executive branch, is more in line with our current leadership. Perhaps we can establish connections with him?
- @sukiman_connections1: The older Radicals, men like Sidik and Sartono, are seen as more cooperative than other <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> leaders by the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> legislative branch. Perhaps we can use them to [? if masyumi_ideology >= 41: appease the Sukimanite <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> leadership? ?][? if masyumi_ideology <= 40: empower Sukiman? ?]
- @natsir_connections1: The younger Moderates, led by Wilopo, are seen as more cooperative than other <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> leaders by the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> executive branch. Perhaps we can use Wilopo to [? if masyumi_ideology <= 40: appease the Natsirite <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> leadership? ?][? if masyumi_ideology >= 41: empower Natsir? ?]
-

@masyumi_ties
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1
go-to: masyumi_op if not pni_in_government and masyumi_in_government; masyumi_1 if pni_in_government and masyumi_in_government

@masyumi_op
on-arrival: masyumi_relation += 5*(1 - dissent); psii_relation += 3*(1 - dissent)

We are currently in opposition to the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> and our relations remain cold. However this may change.

@masyumi_1
on-arrival: masyumi_relation += 8*(1 - dissent); psii_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

We are currently coalition partners with them, so improving relations comes naturally.

@sukiman_connections
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1 and wilopo_dissent <= 20
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources <= 1: Not enough resources. ?][? if wilopo_dissent >= 20: The party is unwilling. ?]
on-arrival: resources -= 1

